Metadata-Version: 1.0
Name: gerrymetrics
Version: 0.1.2
Summary: Lots of metrics for quantifying gerrymandering
Home-page: https://github.com/PrincetonUniversity/gerrymandertests
Author: Princeton Gerrymandering Project
Author-email: wtadler@princeton.edu
License: GNU General Public License v3.0
Description: Code for running 16 different metrics for measuring partisan gerrymandering, including:
        
        - Mean-median difference and variant:
           - Mean-median difference
           - Equal vote weight
        - Lopsided margins (two-sample _t_-test on win margins)
        - Bootstrap (Monte Carlo) simulation
        - Declination variants
           - Declination
           - Declination (buffered)
           - Declination variant
           - Declination variant (buffered)
        - Efficiency gap variants
           - Efficiency gap
           - Difference gap
           - Loss gap
           - Surplus gap
           - Vote-centric gap
           - Vote-centric gap 2
           - Tau gap
        - Partisan bias
        
Platform: UNKNOWN
